    "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
    "body" : "<p>This works because <code>Integer::min</code> resolves to an implementation of the <code>Comparator&lt;Integer&gt;</code> interface.</p>\n\n<p>The method reference of <code>Integer::min</code> resolves to <code>Integer.min(int a, int b)</code>, resolved to <code>IntBinaryOperator</code>, and presumably autoboxing occurs somewhere making it a <code>BinaryOperator&lt;Integer&gt;</code>.</p>\n\n<p>And the <code>min()</code> resp <code>max()</code> methods of the <code>Stream&lt;Integer&gt;</code> ask the <code>Comparator&lt;Integer&gt;</code> interface to be implemented.<br>\nNow this resolves to the single method <code>Integer compareTo(Integer o1, Integer o2)</code>. Which is of type <code>BinaryOperator&lt;Integer&gt;</code>.</p>\n\n<p>And thus the magic has happened as both methods are a <code>BinaryOperator&lt;Integer&gt;</code>.</p>\n"
  }, {
