      "comment_id" : 34372426,
      "content_license" : "CC BY-SA 3.0",
      "body" : "I think the underlying problem is the type signature of <code>Comparator.compare</code>. It should return an <code>enum</code> of <code>{LessThan, GreaterThan, Equal}</code>, not an <code>int</code>. That way, the functional interface wouldn&#39;t actually match and you would get a compile error. IOW: the type signature of <code>Comparator.compare</code> doesn&#39;t adequately capture the semantics of what it means to compare two objects, and thus other interfaces which have absolutely nothing to do with comparing objects accidentally have the same type signature."
    }, {
